Package: palyoplot
Type: Package
Title: Visualization and Multi-Axis Stratigraphic Plotting of
        Quaternary Science Data
Version: 0.0.17
Authors@R: person("Anna", "Klimaszewski-Patterson", email = "anna.kp@csus.edu",
  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Anna Klimaszewski-Patterson <anna.kp@csus.edu>
Description: Palyoplot adds publication-quality Quaternary science data visualization 
    functions to the statistical program R. Palyoplot implements customizable stratigraphical 
    diagramming of proxy records such as pollen, sedimentary charcoal, and diatoms. It allows 
    for user-defined groups and ordered taxa, custom color application by group/taxa, multiple 
    y-axes (ex: depth and age), and customizable y and x-axis intervals leveraging the R 
    language's extensive graphics libraries. Palyoplot creates presentation-ready graphics in 
    a variety of graphical formats (.jpg, .png, .pdf, etc), and is appropriate for routine and 
    scientific research use.
Imports: data.table, ggplot2, gridExtra, tidyr, scales
Depends: R (>= 4.3), gtable, grid, dplyr
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Author: Anna Klimaszewski-Patterson [aut, cre]
